<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> in a big way • in a great way</xh5><p> <i>in a big way</i>—(coll.) 1. on a large scale: The company should be frugal, they say, but when it does invest it should do so <u>in a big way</u>. 2. with great eagerness or enthusiasm: Derek is crazy to take up dancing <u>in a big way</u> again. He adores all this old-time dancing.</p><p> <i>in a great way—</i>1. <i>(UK dated)</i> living on a grand scale: She was very well married, to a gentleman <u>in a great way</u>, near Bristol, who kept two carriages! 2. <i>(coll.)</i> extremely well: Most of us will never do great things, but we can all do small things <u>in a great way</u>.</p> </entry>
